# Bronze++

Bronze++ data product consumes data from 4 archive buckets of bronze.

The 4 archive buckets are listed below:

- **DEV:** project - 0001, account - account=0(.+)$
- **ITG:** project - 0002, account - account==0(.+)$
- **PROD:** project - 0001, account - account==5(.+)$

## Archive Bucket Path

| Type                | S3 Path                                                                                       |
|---------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| events              | s3://cscranalytics-prod-archive/cdm/v1.0/events/{originatorGun}/{eventGun}/{account}/project={project} |
| posts               | s3://cscranalytics-prod-archive/cdm/v1.0/posts/{originatorGun}/{eventGun}/{account}/project={project}  |
| originatorContextPath | s3://cscranalytics-prod-archive/cdm/v1.0/originatorContext/{originatorGun}/{eventGun}/{account/project={project} |
| privacy             | s3://cscranalytics-prod-archive/cdm/v1.0/privacy/{originatorGun}/{eventGun}/{account}/project={project} |

Databricks job loads data into Bronze++ unity catalog where managed tables point to s3 buckets of dataos-{env}-one-cloud-shared buckets.

Firmware originators (FW): Imagingdevice, SOL-Sirius On Linux (service eventing, domain eventing).
